<font color="#FF0000">NEVER FORGET</font><br>
<tt>Fri Feb 13 12:34:11 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Never forget<br><br>
Thursday, Congress honored American POWs and some 2,000 soldiers who are still missing in action. Twenty five years ago to the day, the first prisoners were freed from North Vietnam, including Rep. Sam Johnson, Texas Republican, who was saluted on the House floor.<br>
Over at the Republican National Committee, Chairman Jim Nicholson wanted to ensure that others would remember those days as well.<br>
Thursday, the striking black POW-MIA flag was raised over RNC headquarters to mark the anniversary.<br>
The flag, Mr. Nicholson said, &quot;will send a powerful message to the thousands of commuters, tourists and Capitol Hill staffers who use the Capitol South Metro station every day. As long as I'm chairman, the flag will fly every day.&quot;<br>
The chairman is both a Vietnam vet and a former Army Ranger.<br><br>
Cook Barela
